PN,46408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F464A1776625869
OL,3,CThe main pledges from Wales' smaller
OL,4,Cparties ahead of the Senedd Election
OL,6,FTheir manifesto starts by stating that
OL,7,F"Welsh democracy is not working" and
OL,8,Fthey would introduce a number of
OL,9,F"democratic reforms", including
OL,10,Fintroducing a directly elected Welsh
OL,11,FFirst Minister and scrapping bodies
OL,12,Fsuch as the Ombudsman and Social Care
OL,13,FWales.
OL,15,FSome of their key policies include
OL,16,Fabolishing the 45% additional rate of
OL,17,Fincome tax and provide up to #1,500
OL,18,Fper month for parents of children aged
OL,19,F0`2 who choose to care for their child
OL,20,Fat home.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,465,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F464A1776625869
OL,3,CThe main pledges from Wales' smaller
OL,4,Cparties ahead of the Senedd Election
OL,6,FAs for healthcare, Propel believes in
OL,7,F"prevention focused healthcare" and
OL,8,Fsays it would introduce a yearly
OL,9,Fhealth check for every person in
OL,10,FWales. Their full manifesto can be
OL,11,Ffound here.
OL,13,FTrade Union & Socialist Coalition -
OL,14,FTUSC
OL,16,FThere will be five TUSC candidates
OL,17,Fstanding at the Senedd Election across
OL,18,Ftwo constituencies.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
